Odaily Planet Daily News According to official news, FLock officially launched the Elite Trainer program, recruiting outstanding ML engineers, AI developers and data scientists worldwide to jointly promote the development of decentralized AI training. The program will attract top talents to become training nodes, participate in on-chain federated learning in the AI ​​Training Arena, and improve the efficiency and accuracy of AI training.
AI recruitment targets include:
- Kaggle/Numerai Grandmasters or Masters, and other AI challenge/competition winners;
- Highly influential GitHub AI/ML contributors, top developers on platforms such as LeetCode and HackerRank;
- Scholars who have published research results in top AI conferences/journals such as NeurIPS, ICML, CVPR, and TAI.
Participants will receive an exclusive training wallet and 200,000 FLOCK tokens (provided by the FLock Foundation, non-transferable during training, and the specific number may be adjusted). In addition, trainers can share 50% of the rewards after the completion of the training task, which are paid in the form of FLOCK tokens, and can experience new features in advance.
